{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 0, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "PullRequestComment", "identifier": ["torvalds", "linux", 1], "url": "https://github.com/torvalds/linux/pull/1", "semantic_text": "An example of ignoring the rule when we need to and a good illustration of where tooling might need to support export default.\n\nSince vite is going to be pluggable with other tooling `export default` is a good call because it means that libraries which use it will be able to continue using it even if the name changes", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1618019763.0}
